#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:2
msgid "jobs - print currently running jobs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:7
msgid "jobs [OPTIONS] [PID | %JOBID]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:13
msgid "Description"
msgstr "描述"

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:17
msgid ""
"NOTE: This page documents the fish builtin ``jobs``. To see the "
"documentation on any non-fish versions, use ``command man jobs``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:20
msgid ""
"``jobs`` prints a list of the currently running :ref:`jobs <syntax-job-"
"control>` and their status."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:22
msgid "``jobs`` accepts the following options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:24
msgid "**-c** or **--command**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:25
msgid "Prints the command name for each process in jobs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:27
msgid "**-g** or **--group**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:28
msgid "Only prints the group ID of each job."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:30
msgid "**-l** or **--last**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:31
msgid "Prints only the last job to be started."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:33
msgid "**-p** or **--pid**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:34
msgid "Prints the process ID for each process in all jobs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:36
msgid "**-q** or **--query**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:37
msgid ""
"Prints no output for evaluation of jobs by exit status only. For "
"compatibility with old fish versions this is also **--quiet** (but this is "
"deprecated)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:39
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:40
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr "顯示此指令的幫助資訊。"

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:42
msgid ""
"On systems that support this feature, jobs will print the CPU usage of each "
"job since the last command was executed. The CPU usage is expressed as a "
"percentage of full CPU activity. Note that on multiprocessor systems, the "
"total activity may be more than 100\\%."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:44
msgid ""
"Arguments of the form *PID* or *%JOBID* restrict the output to jobs with the "
"selected process identifiers or job numbers respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:46
msgid ""
"If the output of ``jobs`` is redirected or if it is part of a command "
"substitution, the column header that is usually printed is omitted, making "
"it easier to parse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:48
msgid ""
"The exit status of ``jobs`` is ``0`` if there are running background jobs "
"and ``1`` otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:51
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:53
msgid ""
"``jobs`` outputs a summary of the current jobs, such as two long-running "
"tasks in this example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/jobs.rst:55
msgid ""
"Job Group   State   Command\n"
"2   26012   running nc -l 55232 < /dev/random &\n"
"1   26011   running python tests/test_11.py &"
msgstr ""
